# Python Code Guidelines

## Type Annotations

- Add type annotations to ALL functions, parameters, and return values
- Use Python 3.9 compatible type annotations:
  - Use `Union[Type1, Type2]` instead of `Type1 | Type2`
- Use type annotations instead of comments to clarify variable types
- The comment `# %%` is used to delimit notebook cells in standard scripts

## Documentation

- Follow the existing docstring style (Google style in this project)
- Keep docstrings informative but concise

## Testing

- Ensure all code passes the provided tests
- Don't modify test functions unless explicitly instructed
